race.comment: NAILED'EM (5) just missed fresh before an impressive victory last start at Albany when dropping back to this trip. He has the speed to roll across from the draw and the way he put them away last start was very good. Looks as though he can work through the grades. BANNERED (3) is another who can sit on the speed, just missing in a stronger race at Pinjarra 15 days ago. Nottle's claim comes in handy and if he's able to find the front with ease, he'll be very hard to peg back. LADY COCO (8) closed well last start over 1000m and should appreciate the slight rise in trip this time around. Galati hops back on board and he has a good record aboard the mare. Won't be far away. SANCTIONS (6) is ticking along nicely and can be in the finish. INSYDE SUCCESS (2) comes through a good form race last start at Albany where he jumped favourite. Won't be far away.
